<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Intelligence Sprint — LXD Completion Pack</title>
<style>
*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

:root {
  --bg: #F4F5F9;
  --surface: #FFFFFF;
  --ink: #0A0F1E;
  --ink-mid: #2E3650;
  --muted: #6B7494;
  --light: #ADADC8;
  --rule: #D0D4E4;
  --signal: #0E2D6B;
  --signal-mid: #1A4DA8;
  --signal-lt: #E8EDF8;
  --signal-rule: #B5C8F4;
  --green: #1A5C38;
  --green-lt: #E6EFE9;
  --green-rule: #9FD4B8;
  --amber: #7A4500;
  --amber-lt: #FDF5E6;
  --amber-rule: #D4A85C;
  --purple: #4A2D8A;
  --purple-lt: #F0EAFB;
  --purple-rule: #C8B8F4;
  --red: #7C2D12;
  --red-lt: #FDF0EC;
}

body {
  font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
  background: var(--bg);
  color: var(--ink);
  min-height: 100vh;
  font-size: 13px;
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
}

.header {
  background: var(--signal);
  padding: 0 32px;
  height: 56px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: 100;
}

.header-title {
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: #fff;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 10px;
}

.header-tag {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
  padding: 3px 8px;
  border-radius: 4px;
}

.tabs {
  display: flex;
  background: var(--surface);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  padding: 0 32px;
  overflow-x: auto;
}

.tab {
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 500;
  padding: 14px 20px;
  border: none;
  background: transparent;
  color: var(--muted);
  cursor: pointer;
  border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
  white-space: nowrap;
  transition: all 0.15s;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 7px;
}

.tab.active {
  color: var(--ink);
  border-bottom-color: var(--signal);
  font-weight: 600;
}

.tab:hover:not(.active) { color: var(--ink-mid); }

.tab-dot {
  width: 8px;
  height: 8px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.panel { display: none; }
.panel.visible { display: block; }

.content {
  max-width: 760px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 36px 32px 64px;
}

.section-eyebrow {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.14em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--muted);
  margin-bottom: 6px;
}

.section-title {
  font-size: 22px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  color: var(--ink);
  margin-bottom: 6px;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.section-sub {
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.65;
  margin-bottom: 28px;
  max-width: 560px;
}

.info-card {
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 14px 18px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
  display: flex;
  gap: 12px;
  align-items: flex-start;
  font-size: 13px;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.info-label {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  white-space: nowrap;
  padding-top: 2px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.divider {
  border: none;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  margin: 24px 0;
}

/* ── INSIGHT BRIEF TEMPLATE ── */
.brief-template {
  background: var(--surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.bt-header {
  background: var(--signal);
  padding: 16px 20px;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
}

.bt-title {
  font-size: 15px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #fff;
}

.bt-badge {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
  padding: 4px 10px;
  border-radius: 4px;
}

.bt-body {
  padding: 20px;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 16px;
}

.bt-field {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 6px;
}

.bt-field-header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
}

.bt-label {
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--signal-mid);
}

.bt-required {
  font-size: 10px;
  color: var(--red);
  font-weight: 600;
}

.bt-optional {
  font-size: 10px;
  color: var(--muted);
}

.bt-input {
  background: var(--bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 10px 14px;
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--ink);
  font-family: inherit;
  resize: vertical;
  min-height: 72px;
  transition: border-color 0.15s;
  outline: none;
  width: 100%;
}

.bt-input:focus {
  border-color: var(--signal-mid);
  background: var(--surface);
}

.bt-prompt {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.55;
  font-style: italic;
  padding: 8px 12px;
  background: var(--signal-lt);
  border-radius: 6px;
  border-left: 3px solid var(--signal-mid);
}

.bt-short-inputs {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 12px;
}

.bt-short {
  background: var(--bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 10px 14px;
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--ink);
  font-family: inherit;
  transition: border-color 0.15s;
  outline: none;
  width: 100%;
}

.bt-short:focus {
  border-color: var(--signal-mid);
  background: var(--surface);
}

.bt-footer {
  padding: 14px 20px;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  background: var(--bg);
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
}

.bt-submit {
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #fff;
  background: var(--signal);
  border: none;
  padding: 10px 24px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background 0.15s;
}

.bt-submit:hover { background: #143E9A; }

.bt-word-count {
  font-size: 11px;
  color: var(--muted);
}

.design-note {
  background: var(--signal-lt);
  border-left: 4px solid var(--signal-mid);
  border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
  padding: 12px 16px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--ink);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.design-note-label {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--signal-mid);
  margin-bottom: 5px;
}

.quality-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 10px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.quality-card {
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 12px 14px;
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
}

.quality-label {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  margin-bottom: 6px;
}

.quality-item {
  font-size: 12px;
  line-height: 1.5;
  display: flex;
  gap: 6px;
  margin-bottom: 4px;
  align-items: flex-start;
}

.quality-item:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

/* ── BASELINE QUESTIONS ── */
.q-card {
  background: var(--surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.q-header {
  padding: 12px 18px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 12px;
}

.q-num {
  width: 28px;
  height: 28px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #fff;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.q-meta { flex: 1; }

.q-title {
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--ink);
  margin-bottom: 2px;
}

.q-when { font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); }

.q-body { padding: 16px 18px; }

.q-text {
  font-size: 15px;
  color: var(--ink);
  line-height: 1.55;
  font-style: italic;
  margin-bottom: 14px;
  padding-left: 12px;
  border-left: 3px solid var(--rule);
}

.q-scale {
  display: flex;
  gap: 8px;
  margin-bottom: 14px;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.scale-opt {
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 500;
  padding: 6px 14px;
  border-radius: 20px;
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  background: var(--bg);
  color: var(--muted);
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: all 0.15s;
}

.scale-opt:hover, .scale-opt.sel {
  background: var(--signal-lt);
  border-color: var(--signal-rule);
  color: var(--signal-mid);
  font-weight: 600;
}

.q-note {
  font-size: 11px;
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.55;
  padding: 8px 12px;
  background: var(--bg);
  border-radius: 6px;
}

.q-note strong { color: var(--ink); }

.open-text {
  width: 100%;
  background: var(--bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 10px 14px;
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--ink);
  font-family: inherit;
  resize: vertical;
  min-height: 80px;
  outline: none;
  transition: border-color 0.15s;
  margin-bottom: 14px;
}

.open-text:focus {
  border-color: var(--signal-mid);
  background: var(--surface);
}

.baseline-summary {
  background: var(--signal-lt);
  border: 1px solid var(--signal-rule);
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 16px 20px;
  margin-top: 24px;
}

.bs-title {
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--signal-mid);
  margin-bottom: 12px;
}

.bs-scores {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3,1fr);
  gap: 10px;
}

.bs-score {
  background: var(--surface);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 12px;
  text-align: center;
}

.bs-num {
  font-size: 26px;
  font-weight: 800;
  color: var(--signal-mid);
  line-height: 1;
}

.bs-label {
  font-size: 10px;
  color: var(--muted);
  margin-top: 4px;
  line-height: 1.4;
}

/* ── EU AI ACT ── */
.eu-hero {
  background: var(--purple);
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 24px 28px;
  margin-bottom: 24px;
}

.eu-hero-label {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.14em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4);
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.eu-hero-title {
  font-size: 20px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #fff;
  margin-bottom: 8px;
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.eu-hero-sub {
  font-size: 13px;
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.deadline-banner {
  background: var(--red-lt);
  border: 1px solid #F4B5A8;
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 12px 16px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
  display: flex;
  gap: 12px;
  align-items: flex-start;
}

.deadline-icon { font-size: 18px; flex-shrink: 0; }

.deadline-label {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--red);
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}

.deadline-text {
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--ink);
  line-height: 1.55;
}

.deadline-text strong { color: var(--red); font-weight: 700; }

.article-card {
  background: var(--surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-radius: 10px;
  overflow: hidden;
  margin-bottom: 14px;
}

.article-header {
  padding: 12px 16px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  background: var(--purple-lt);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 10px;
}

.article-num {
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--purple);
  background: rgba(74,45,138,0.1);
  padding: 3px 8px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.article-title {
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--ink);
}

.article-body {
  padding: 14px 16px;
}

.article-text {
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--ink-mid);
  line-height: 1.65;
  margin-bottom: 12px;
}

.article-connection {
  background: var(--purple-lt);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--purple);
  border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
  padding: 10px 14px;
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--ink);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.article-connection-label {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--purple);
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}

.addendum-box {
  background: var(--surface);
  border: 2px solid var(--purple);
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 20px 22px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.addendum-label {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--purple);
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.addendum-title {
  font-size: 16px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--ink);
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.addendum-text {
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--ink-mid);
  line-height: 1.7;
}

.addendum-text strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 600; }

.copy-btn {
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--purple);
  background: var(--purple-lt);
  border: 1px solid var(--purple-rule);
  padding: 8px 16px;
  border-radius: 7px;
  cursor: pointer;
  margin-top: 14px;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 6px;
  transition: all 0.15s;
}

.copy-btn:hover { background: var(--purple); color: #fff; }
.copy-btn.copied { background: var(--green-lt); color: var(--green); border-color: var(--green-rule); }

.buyer-shift {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
  gap: 12px;
  align-items: center;
  margin-top: 20px;
}

.buyer-card {
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 14px;
}

.buyer-label {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  margin-bottom: 6px;
}

.buyer-role {
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--ink);
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}

.buyer-budget {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.4;
}

.buyer-arrow {
  font-size: 20px;
  color: var(--purple);
  text-align: center;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

@media(max-width:600px){
  .content { padding: 24px 16px 48px; }
  .tabs { padding: 0 16px; }
  .bt-short-inputs { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .quality-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .bs-scores { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .buyer-shift { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .buyer-arrow { display: none; }
  .header { padding: 0 20px; }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="header">
  <div class="header-title">
    Intelligence Sprint
    <span class="header-tag">LXD Completion Pack</span>
  </div>
  <div style="font-size:11px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.35);">3 gaps fixed</div>
</div>

<div class="tabs">
  <button class="tab active" onclick="show('template')">
    <div class="tab-dot" style="background:var(--signal-mid);"></div>
    Insight brief template
  </button>
  <button class="tab" onclick="show('baseline')">
    <div class="tab-dot" style="background:var(--green);"></div>
    Baseline questions
  </button>
  <button class="tab" onclick="show('euai')">
    <div class="tab-dot" style="background:var(--purple);"></div>
    EU AI Act angle
  </button>
</div>

<!-- ── INSIGHT BRIEF TEMPLATE ── -->
<div id="panel-template" class="panel visible">
  <div class="content">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Gap 2 — fixed</div>
    <div class="section-title">Insight brief template</div>
    <div class="section-sub">The single most important artefact in the Intelligence Sprint. Without it, week 2 produces inconsistent submissions that product management cannot evaluate. With it, every engineering insight arrives in a format that is immediately legible to a commercial audience.</div>

    <div class="info-card" style="background:var(--signal-lt);border:1px solid var(--signal-rule);">
      <div class="info-label" style="color:var(--signal-mid);">How to use</div>
      <div style="color:var(--ink);font-size:13px;line-height:1.6;">Send this template to all participating teams at the week 1 kick-off. They complete and submit it by the end of week 2. The same template is used by product management to score and rank briefs in week 4. The four sections are non-negotiable — incomplete submissions are returned, not scored.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="design-note">
      <div class="design-note-label">The design principle behind the template</div>
      The four sections are ordered deliberately. Context before observation. Observation before implication. Implication before ask. This forces engineers to translate technical knowledge into commercial language in the right sequence — not to lead with the technical detail that product management can't evaluate, but to start with the programme context that makes the observation immediately legible.
    </div>

    <div class="brief-template">
      <div class="bt-header">
        <div class="bt-title">Intelligence Sprint — Insight Brief</div>
        <div class="bt-badge">Week 2 submission</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bt-body">

        <div class="bt-field">
          <div class="bt-field-header">
            <div class="bt-label">Section 1 — Programme context</div>
            <div class="bt-required">Required</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bt-prompt">Which engineering programme, platform, or supplier relationship does this insight connect to? Name it specifically — not a general area but a live, active context your team is working in right now.</div>
          <textarea class="bt-input" placeholder="Example: ADAS domain controller programme for [OEM], currently in validation phase. Supplier: [Supplier name]. Platform: [Platform name]. Status: active, Q3 2026 delivery." rows="3"></textarea>
        </div>

        <div class="bt-field">
          <div class="bt-field-header">
            <div class="bt-label">Section 2 — Technical observation</div>
            <div class="bt-required">Required</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bt-prompt">What have you observed that others haven't acted on? Be specific. Name the system, the behaviour, the measurement, or the pattern. Avoid jargon where possible — write it as if explaining to a product manager who understands automotive but not your specific domain.</div>
          <textarea class="bt-input" placeholder="Example: Our sensor fusion algorithm degrades significantly below 15°C in wet conditions. This affects object classification accuracy by approximately 23% in real-world testing — a figure that does not appear in our current validation report because the test protocol uses dry-surface scenarios only." rows="4"></textarea>
        </div>

        <div class="bt-field">
          <div class="bt-field-header">
            <div class="bt-label">Section 3 — Commercial or regulatory implication</div>
            <div class="bt-required">Required</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bt-prompt">What does this observation mean commercially, competitively, or from a regulatory standpoint? Who is affected — a customer, a regulator, a procurement decision, a product roadmap? Quantify where possible. This is the section that makes your brief actionable for product management.</div>
          <textarea class="bt-input" placeholder="Example: If this degradation is not addressed before the EURO NCAP 2026 assessment, we risk a downgrade from 5-star to 4-star in adverse weather performance. This affects the commercial positioning of [programme] in the Nordics and UK markets, where adverse weather usage is a stated OEM selling point. Estimated commercial impact: [€ range] in lost premium positioning." rows="4"></textarea>
        </div>

        <div class="bt-field">
          <div class="bt-field-header">
            <div class="bt-label">Section 4 — Supporting data</div>
            <div class="bt-required">Required from week 3</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bt-prompt">What data supports your observation? This can be test results, validation logs, supplier scorecards, JIRA data, ASPICE compliance records, or any structured data your team already has access to. In week 3 you'll receive a one-page job aid showing three specific views that help translate this data into a commercial argument.</div>
          <textarea class="bt-input" placeholder="Example: Test bench results from [date], file: [reference]. Sensor performance log Q2 2026. JIRA ticket count for classification failures: [number]. Supplier quality report [reference]." rows="3"></textarea>
        </div>

        <div class="bt-field">
          <div class="bt-field-header">
            <div class="bt-label">Section 5 — What a good outcome looks like</div>
            <div class="bt-optional">Optional but scored</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bt-prompt">If product management acts on this insight, what changes? What decision gets made differently? What gets added to the roadmap, the test protocol, the supplier brief, or the regulatory submission? One or two sentences. This is not a solution proposal — it is a description of the decision you want to enable.</div>
          <textarea class="bt-input" placeholder="Example: Product management adds adverse weather validation to the Q4 test protocol. Procurement issues a revised supplier brief requiring performance certification in sub-15°C wet conditions. EURO NCAP submission reflects actual real-world performance." rows="3"></textarea>
        </div>

        <div class="bt-short-inputs">
          <div>
            <div class="bt-label" style="margin-bottom:6px;">Team name</div>
            <input class="bt-short" type="text" placeholder="Team or department name">
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="bt-label" style="margin-bottom:6px;">Submission date</div>
            <input class="bt-short" type="date">
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
      <div class="bt-footer">
        <div class="bt-word-count">All required sections must be complete before submission is accepted</div>
        <button class="bt-submit">Submit insight brief →</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">

    <div class="section-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:10px;">How product management scores submissions</div>
    <div class="quality-grid">
      <div class="quality-card" style="background:var(--signal-lt);border-color:var(--signal-rule);">
        <div class="quality-label" style="color:var(--signal-mid);">Strong submission — scores high</div>
        <div class="quality-item" style="color:var(--ink-mid);"><span style="color:var(--green);font-weight:700;">✓</span>Anchored to a named, live programme</div>
        <div class="quality-item" style="color:var(--ink-mid);"><span style="color:var(--green);font-weight:700;">✓</span>Technical observation is specific and measurable</div>
        <div class="quality-item" style="color:var(--ink-mid);"><span style="color:var(--green);font-weight:700;">✓</span>Commercial implication names a real impact</div>
        <div class="quality-item" style="color:var(--ink-mid);"><span style="color:var(--green);font-weight:700;">✓</span>At least one data reference from a real source</div>
        <div class="quality-item" style="color:var(--ink-mid);"><span style="color:var(--green);font-weight:700;">✓</span>Outcome description enables a specific decision</div>
      </div>
      <div class="quality-card" style="background:var(--red-lt);border-color:#F4B5A8;">
        <div class="quality-label" style="color:var(--red);">Weak submission — returned for revision</div>
        <div class="quality-item" style="color:var(--ink-mid);"><span style="color:var(--red);font-weight:700;">✗</span>General area rather than named programme</div>
        <div class="quality-item" style="color:var(--ink-mid);"><span style="color:var(--red);font-weight:700;">✗</span>Technical observation without a measurement</div>
        <div class="quality-item" style="color:var(--ink-mid);"><span style="color:var(--red);font-weight:700;">✗</span>Implication uses vague language: "could affect"</div>
        <div class="quality-item" style="color:var(--ink-mid);"><span style="color:var(--red);font-weight:700;">✗</span>No data — only the engineer's opinion</div>
        <div class="quality-item" style="color:var(--ink-mid);"><span style="color:var(--red);font-weight:700;">✗</span>Outcome is a solution proposal, not a decision</div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<!-- ── BASELINE QUESTIONS ── -->
<div id="panel-baseline" class="panel">
  <div class="content">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Gap 7 — fixed</div>
    <div class="section-title">Baseline questions — engineering version</div>
    <div class="section-sub">Three questions administered before week 1 begins. Repeated after week 4. Without them the case study has no proof of change. These are different from the Revenue Cup baseline — they are written specifically for an engineering mindset and an engineering-to-commercial translation gap.</div>

    <div class="info-card" style="background:var(--green-lt);border:1px solid var(--green-rule);">
      <div class="info-label" style="color:var(--green);">How to use</div>
      <div style="color:var(--ink);font-size:13px;line-height:1.6;">Add to the week 1 kick-off email. Same questions in the week 4 review day follow-up. The delta between baseline and final is your primary case study metric. Question 3 is open text only — the answers are your most powerful testimonial material.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="q-card">
      <div class="q-header">
        <div class="q-num" style="background:var(--signal-mid);">1</div>
        <div class="q-meta">
          <div class="q-title">Commercial translation confidence</div>
          <div class="q-when">Asked: Before week 1 · Repeated: After week 4</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-body">
        <div class="q-text">On a scale of 1–5, how confident are you that you could explain the commercial or regulatory implication of a technical observation you made this week — in a way that a product manager could act on?</div>
        <div class="q-scale">
          <div class="scale-opt" onclick="selectOpt(this,1)">1 — Not at all</div>
          <div class="scale-opt" onclick="selectOpt(this,1)">2 — Slightly</div>
          <div class="scale-opt" onclick="selectOpt(this,1)">3 — Somewhat</div>
          <div class="scale-opt" onclick="selectOpt(this,1)">4 — Quite confident</div>
          <div class="scale-opt" onclick="selectOpt(this,1)">5 — Very confident</div>
        </div>
        <div class="q-note"><strong>What this measures:</strong> The engineering-to-commercial translation gap — the primary skill gap the Sprint addresses. Target delta: +1.5 after the programme. Below +0.5 means the insight brief template or the week 3 job aid needs redesigning.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="q-card">
      <div class="q-header">
        <div class="q-num" style="background:var(--signal-mid);">2</div>
        <div class="q-meta">
          <div class="q-title">Belief that insights reach product management</div>
          <div class="q-when">Asked: Before week 1 · Repeated: After week 4</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-body">
        <div class="q-text">On a scale of 1–5, how much do you believe that a technical observation from your team would be seriously considered by product management and potentially acted on?</div>
        <div class="q-scale">
          <div class="scale-opt" onclick="selectOpt(this,2)">1 — Not at all</div>
          <div class="scale-opt" onclick="selectOpt(this,2)">2 — Unlikely</div>
          <div class="scale-opt" onclick="selectOpt(this,2)">3 — Possibly</div>
          <div class="scale-opt" onclick="selectOpt(this,2)">4 — Probably</div>
          <div class="scale-opt" onclick="selectOpt(this,2)">5 — Definitely</div>
        </div>
        <div class="q-note"><strong>What this measures:</strong> Environment and motivation gap — whether engineers believe the channel now exists. The most important baseline question. If this doesn't shift after four weeks the sponsor's signal at the review day wasn't strong enough — or the PM didn't visibly engage with the submitted briefs.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="q-card">
      <div class="q-header">
        <div class="q-num" style="background:var(--signal-mid);">3</div>
        <div class="q-meta">
          <div class="q-title">Last time a technical observation led to a commercial decision</div>
          <div class="q-when">Asked: Before week 1 only — open text</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-body">
        <div class="q-text">When was the last time a technical observation you made in your work led to a change in a commercial or product decision? Describe what happened in one or two sentences. If you can't think of an example, say so.</div>
        <textarea class="open-text" placeholder="Write your answer here..."></textarea>
        <div class="q-note"><strong>What this measures:</strong> Baseline state of the intelligence pathway. If most engineers answer "I can't think of an example" — that is your most powerful case study opening line. If several have examples, those examples become your benchmark for what the Sprint is designed to replicate systematically. Either answer is valuable. This is also your most powerful testimonial field.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">

    <div class="baseline-summary">
      <div class="bs-title">Day-30 measurement — what to compare</div>
      <div class="bs-scores">
        <div class="bs-score">
          <div class="bs-num" style="color:var(--signal-mid);">Q1</div>
          <div class="bs-label">Commercial translation confidence — baseline vs week 4. Target delta: +1.5</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bs-score">
          <div class="bs-num" style="color:var(--signal-mid);">Q2</div>
          <div class="bs-label">Belief insights reach PM — baseline vs week 4. Target delta: +1.0</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bs-score">
          <div class="bs-num" style="color:var(--signal-mid);">Q3</div>
          <div class="bs-label">Pre-programme stories — used as case study opening, not delta measurement</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<!-- ── EU AI ACT ── -->
<div id="panel-euai" class="panel">
  <div class="content">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Gap 9 — fixed</div>
    <div class="section-title">EU AI Act compliance angle</div>
    <div class="section-sub">The Intelligence Sprint was designed as an innovation programme. It is also — without any design changes — a compliance tool. This tab shows how to present that angle, who the second buyer is, and the exact paragraph to add to your brief.</div>

    <div class="eu-hero">
      <div class="eu-hero-label">EU AI Act · High-risk systems · Article 4</div>
      <div class="eu-hero-title">ADAS engineering teams are legally required to have AI literacy by August 2026.</div>
      <div class="eu-hero-sub">The Intelligence Sprint surfaces technical insights about AI system performance and limitations — which is precisely what Article 4 compliance documentation requires. You built a compliance tool without knowing it.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="deadline-banner">
      <div class="deadline-icon">⚠️</div>
      <div>
        <div class="deadline-label">Enforcement deadline</div>
        <div class="deadline-text">EU AI Act Article 4 AI literacy requirements apply to organisations deploying high-risk AI systems from <strong>August 2, 2026</strong>. ADAS systems are explicitly listed as high-risk under Annex III. Engineering teams working on these systems must demonstrate AI literacy — including the ability to identify and communicate AI system limitations.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="article-card">
      <div class="article-header">
        <div class="article-num">Article 4</div>
        <div class="article-title">AI literacy requirement — what it actually requires</div>
      </div>
      <div class="article-body">
        <div class="article-text">Article 4 requires that providers and deployers of high-risk AI systems ensure their staff have sufficient AI literacy to understand the capabilities and limitations of the AI systems they work with — including the ability to identify when AI system outputs may be unreliable, incomplete, or require human oversight.</div>
        <div class="article-connection">
          <div class="article-connection-label">How the Intelligence Sprint addresses this</div>
          When an ADAS engineer submits an insight brief describing a sensor fusion degradation pattern, a classification failure mode, or a validation gap — they are demonstrating exactly the AI literacy Article 4 requires. The Intelligence Sprint creates a structured, documented record of this capability across an engineering team. That record is Article 4 compliance evidence.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="article-card">
      <div class="article-header">
        <div class="article-num">Annex III</div>
        <div class="article-title">High-risk AI systems — ADAS explicitly listed</div>
      </div>
      <div class="article-body">
        <div class="article-text">Annex III of the EU AI Act lists AI systems used in safety components of road traffic management and autonomous vehicles as high-risk. This includes ADAS systems, domain controllers, perception systems, and any AI model used in safety-critical driving functions.</div>
        <div class="article-connection">
          <div class="article-connection-label">What this means for your pilot conversation</div>
          Every ADAS engineering team at an OEM or Tier-1 in Europe is legally required to demonstrate AI literacy by August 2026. The Intelligence Sprint is a structured programme that produces documented evidence of that literacy. It is not just a nice-to-have innovation initiative — it is a compliance deliverable with a legal deadline.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">

    <div class="section-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:10px;">The paragraph to add to your brief</div>
    <div class="addendum-box">
      <div class="addendum-label">Add to the Intelligence Sprint brief — after the "What the pilot produces" section</div>
      <div class="addendum-title">EU AI Act compliance addendum</div>
      <div class="addendum-text">
        For ADAS and SDV engineering teams operating under the EU AI Act, the Intelligence Sprint produces more than commercial intelligence. <strong>Each insight brief submitted by an engineering team is a structured, documented demonstration of AI literacy</strong> — the ability to identify AI system capabilities and limitations and communicate their commercial or regulatory implications.<br><br>
        Under Article 4 of the EU AI Act, organisations deploying high-risk AI systems (which includes ADAS systems under Annex III) must ensure their technical staff have demonstrable AI literacy by <strong>August 2, 2026</strong>. The Intelligence Sprint creates an auditable record of that literacy across your engineering team — aligned with the regulation's requirements and produced in the context of real work, not a training course.<br><br>
        The pilot case study will include a compliance documentation summary showing how participant submissions map to Article 4 literacy requirements — ready to share with your legal or compliance function.
      </div>
      <button class="copy-btn" id="copyBtn" onclick="copyAddendum()">📋 Copy this paragraph</button>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">

    <div class="section-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:10px;">How this changes your buyer and budget source</div>
    <div class="buyer-shift">
      <div class="buyer-card" style="background:var(--signal-lt);border:1px solid var(--signal-rule);">
        <div class="buyer-label" style="color:var(--signal-mid);">Original buyer</div>
        <div class="buyer-role">Head of Engineering Efficiency</div>
        <div class="buyer-budget" style="color:var(--signal-mid);">Innovation and capability budget. Discretionary. Committee approval required above ~€5,000.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="buyer-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="buyer-card" style="background:var(--purple-lt);border:1px solid var(--purple-rule);">
        <div class="buyer-label" style="color:var(--purple);">Second buyer — new</div>
        <div class="buyer-role">Head of Legal, Compliance, or Data Governance</div>
        <div class="buyer-budget" style="color:var(--purple);">Compliance budget. Non-discretionary. Easier to approve because it has a legal deadline attached. Often higher budget authority.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-card" style="background:var(--amber-lt);border:1px solid var(--amber-rule);margin-top:16px;">
      <div class="info-label" style="color:var(--amber);">How to use this in a conversation</div>
      <div style="color:var(--ink);font-size:13px;line-height:1.6;">Don't lead with the compliance angle in your first message — it can feel threatening rather than helpful. Lead with the commercial intelligence problem. When the conversation opens, mention the compliance angle as a secondary benefit: "One thing I should mention — because you're working on ADAS systems, the insight briefs your team produces are also Article 4 compliance evidence. Your legal team might find that useful given the August deadline."</div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<script>
function show(id) {
  ['template','baseline','euai'].forEach(p => {
    document.getElementById('panel-'+p).className = 'panel' + (p === id ? ' visible' : '');
  });
  document.querySelectorAll('.tab').forEach((btn, i) => {
    btn.className = 'tab' + (['template','baseline','euai'][i] === id ? ' active' : '');
  });
}

function selectOpt(el, group) {
  const parent = el.closest('.q-scale');
  parent.querySelectorAll('.scale-opt').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('sel'));
  el.classList.add('sel');
}

function copyAddendum() {
  const text = `For ADAS and SDV engineering teams operating under the EU AI Act, the Intelligence Sprint produces more than commercial intelligence. Each insight brief submitted by an engineering team is a structured, documented demonstration of AI literacy — the ability to identify AI system capabilities and limitations and communicate their commercial or regulatory implications.

Under Article 4 of the EU AI Act, organisations deploying high-risk AI systems (which includes ADAS systems under Annex III) must ensure their technical staff have demonstrable AI literacy by August 2, 2026. The Intelligence Sprint creates an auditable record of that literacy across your engineering team — aligned with the regulation's requirements and produced in the context of real work, not a training course.

The pilot case study will include a compliance documentation summary showing how participant submissions map to Article 4 literacy requirements — ready to share with your legal or compliance function.`;

  navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
    const btn = document.getElementById('copyBtn');
    btn.textContent = '✓ Copied';
    btn.className = 'copy-btn copied';
    setTimeout(() => {
      btn.textContent = '📋 Copy this paragraph';
      btn.className = 'copy-btn';
    }, 2500);
  });
}
</script>
